            "answer_text": "This a simple Pythagorean problem of a right triangle.A^2 + B^2 = C^2.So, you are solving for the hypotenuse.Substituting values:5^2 + 4^2 = 41Take the square root of 41 and you have your answer of 6.4 KM distance that he is from his starting position. ",
